value.Title: Live Sports Broadcasting
value.Description: The Brian Lamb School of Communication will offer a Sports Broadcasting course in the Summer 2022 semester which will train students to run a live broadcast of the Lafayette Aviators baseball games.  Students will have the opportunity to work in the studio, operate cameras on the field, and interview players for segments on The Purdue Channel 5. The schedule would be mid-May to mid-August with 30 home games to cover. Most games are in the evenings (see Aviators schedule on their website for exact days and times). For more information, contact Toni DeAztlan Smith, deaztlan@purdue.edu Lafayette Aviators: https://lafayettebaseball.com/ The Purdue Channel: https://cla.purdue.edu/academic/communication/the-purdue-channel/index.html
